import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    data['minute'] = data['date'].dt.minute
    data['second'] = data['date'].dt.second
    data['time'] = data['hour'] + data['minute']/60 + data['second']/3600
    avg_price = data['price'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axhline(avg_price, color='r', label=f'Average Price: {avg_price:.2f}')
    ax.bar('Average Price', avg_price, color='b')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the average price?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['price'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='price', data=data, ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.set_title('What is the highest and lowest price?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
